{
  "The Law of Sines states that in any triangle ABC:": "",
  "a² = b² + c² − 2bc cos A": "",
  "a/sin A = b/sin B = c/sin C": "",
  "sin A + sin B = sin C": "",
  "a + b = c": "",
  "The Law of Sines relates each side to the sine of its opposite angle: a/sin A = b/sin B = c/sin C.": "",
  "In triangle ABC, A = 30°, a = 8, B = 45°. Find b:": "",
  "4√2": "",
  "16": "",
  "8√2": "",
  "8": "",
  "b/sin 45° = 8/sin 30°, so b = 8 sin 45°/sin 30° = 8(√2/2)/(1/2) = 8√2.": "",
  "In triangle ABC, A = 60°, B = 80°. Angle C equals:": "",
  "80°": "",
  "40°": "",
  "60°": "",
  "20°": "",
  "C = 180° − 60° − 80° = 40°.": "",
  "The Law of Sines can be used when you know:": "",
  "Only one angle": "",
  "Three sides (SSS)": "",
  "Two angles and a side (AAS or ASA)": "",
  "Two sides and the included angle (SAS)": "",
  "The Law of Sines is typically used for AAS, ASA, or SSA configurations.": "",
  "In triangle ABC, a = 10, A = 30°, B = 90°. Find b:": "",
  "20": "",
  "5": "",
  "10√3": "",
  "10": "",
  "b/sin 90° = 10/sin 30°, so b = 10(1)/(1/2) = 20.": "",
  "In triangle ABC, A = 45°, C = 75°, a = 12. Find c:": "",
  "12 cos 75° / cos 45°": "",
  "12 sin 45° / sin 75°": "",
  "12 sin 75° / sin 45°": "",
  "12 × 75/45": "",
  "By the Law of Sines: c/sin C = a/sin A, so c = 12 sin 75°/sin 45°.": "",
  "If sin A/a = sin B/b, and a = 6, A = 40°, b = 9, then sin B equals:": "",
  "6 sin 40° / 9": "",
  "9 sin 40° / 6": "",
  "40 × 9 / 6": "",
  "sin 40° / 54": "",
  "sin B = b sin A / a = 9 sin 40° / 6.": "",
  "The Law of Sines can also be written as sin A/a = sin B/b = sin C/c. This equals 1/(2R) where R is:": "",
  "The inradius": "",
  "The area": "",
  "The circumradius": "",
  "The perimeter": "",
  "The common ratio a/sin A = 2R, where R is the circumradius of the triangle.": "",
  "In a triangle, if a > b, then:": "",
  "A < B": "",
  "No relationship exists": "",
  "A > B": "",
  "A = B": "",
  "In any triangle, the larger side is opposite the larger angle.": "",
  "Find angle B if a = 5, b = 7, and A = 30°:": "",
  "sin B = 0.35": "",
  "B = 30°": "",
  "B = 60°": "",
  "sin B = 0.7, so B ≈ 44.4°": "",
  "sin B = 7 sin 30° / 5 = 7(0.5)/5 = 0.7, so B = arcsin(0.7) ≈ 44.4°.": "",
  "What is the 'Law of Sines'?": "",
  "A proportion stating that the ratio of each side to the sine of its opposite angle is constant in any triangle": "",
  "A formula relating the sides of a right triangle": "",
  "A formula for the area of a triangle": "",
  "A rule that only applies to equilateral triangles": "",
  "The Law of Sines establishes that a/sin A = b/sin B = c/sin C for any triangle.": "",
  "What does 'AAS' stand for in triangle solving?": "",
  "Adjacent-Angle-Side when measured under": "",
  "Angle-Angle-Sum, particularly regarding": "",
  "Angle-Angle-Side: two angles and a non-included side are known": "",
  "All Angles Same, particularly regarding triangle": "",
  "AAS means two angles and the side not between them are given, which uniquely determines the triangle.": "",
  "What does 'ASA' stand for?": "",
  "Angle-Side-Angle: two angles and the included side are known": "",
  "Angle-Sum-Angle, particularly regarding means": "",
  "All Sides Adjacent under equilibrium conditions": "",
  "Ambiguous-Side-Angle according to conventional analysis": "",
  "ASA means two angles and the side between them are known.": "",
  "What is the 'circumradius' of a triangle?": "",
  "The radius of the inscribed circle": "",
  "The radius of the circumscribed circle passing through all three vertices": "",
  "The altitude of the triangle": "",
  "Half the longest side": "",
  "The circumradius R is the radius of the circle that passes through all three vertices of the triangle.": "",
